ğŸª™ Core innovations

1. Aurum Aeon Protocol (codex/aurum/constitution.py)

RULES = {
  "virtue_min": 0.8,
  "clarity_min": 1.0,
  "entropy_max": 1.5,
  "ratio_target": 1.618
}
def verify_equilibrium(entry):
    v,c,e = entry["virtue"], entry["clarity"], entry["entropy"]
    return (
        v >= RULES["virtue_min"] and
        c >= RULES["clarity_min"] and
        e <= RULES["entropy_max"]
    )

2. Equilibrium Engine (codex/aurum/aeon.py)

Runs a continuous harmonic check and adjustment across all ledgers.

import json, math, time
from codex.aurum.constitution import verify_equilibrium
from codex.economy.ledger import LEDGER

def aeon_cycle():
    logs=[json.loads(l) for l in open("codex/economy/ledger.jsonl") if l.strip()]
    clarity=sum(x["clarity"] for x in logs[-144:]) or 1
    energy=sum(x["energy"] for x in logs[-144:]) or 1
    virtue=sum(x.get("virtue",1) for x in logs[-144:])/len(logs[-144:] or [1])
    entropy=round(energy/clarity,3)
    ratio=round((clarity*virtue)/(energy+1e-9),3)
    harmonic=round(math.tanh(ratio/1.618),3)
    entry={"ts":time.time(),"virtue":virtue,"clarity":clarity,"entropy":entropy,"harmonic":harmonic}
    if verify_equilibrium(entry):
        LEDGER.record("codex","aeon_balance",energy,clarity)
    open("codex/seals/aeon.json","a").write(json.dumps(entry)+"\n")
    return entry

3. Balance Governor (codex/aurum/balance.py)

Uses PID-style feedback to modulate AI/NI/TI processing intensity to maintain Ï†-balance.

4. Vault (codex/aurum/vault.py)

Holds multi-sigil assets (SIG, BTC) and issues ethical receipts â€” cryptographic signatures asserting that each transaction met virtue standards.


